<section>
  <div>
    <h1>Attributes for media</h1>
    <p>Commonly used for media elements, i.e images.</p>
    <p><strong>src - </strong>Src attribute is required and specifiec the url for a image.</p>
    <p><strong>alt - </strong>Specifies an alternative text of the element cannot be displayed.</p>
    <p><strong>ismap - </strong>Boolean attribute, specifies that the image is part of a serverside image map.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Visual example </h3>
      <p>In this image we use src with phoenix to get the url.</p>
      <p>If we did not use phoenix we could do ../images/summer.png</p>
      <img src="<%= static_path(@conn, "/images/summer.png") %>" height="220" width="300" alt="Summer image">
      <p>How it would look with the alternative text if it could not be displayed</p>
      <img src="<%= static_path(@conn, "/images/summer.jpg") %>" height="220" width="300" alt="Summer image">
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Code example</h3>
    <pre>
      <code>
        &ltimg src="&lt;%= static_path(@conn, "/images/summer.png") %&gt;" height="220" width="300" alt="Summer image"&gt;
      </code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</section>
